bib_record.title: Isotopic production cross sections of fission residues in Au-197 on proton collisions at 800 A*MeV.

free_txt: University of Santiago Compostela.
All data were taken from the
preprint
Semi-empirical descriptions of the isotope
production in spallation reactions.
The kinetic energies of the fission residues was
determined.
Mass and charge distribution.
-By authors. In order to determine the primary fission
yields produced in the reaction, different corrections
have been applied-
-the losses due to the transmission through the
spectrometer,
-secondary reactions in the target,
-any other layer of matter inside the FRS,
-ionic charge states of the measured isotopes,
-dead time of the data acquisition,
-the efficiency of the detectors.
Two position-sensitive plastic scintillators
and additional multi-wire detectors.
A multi-sample ionization chamber (music).
It is the statistical uncertainty and the
uncertainty due to the correction of secondary
reactions in the target or any other layer of matter
inside the projectile-fragment separator (FRS).
An additional 15% systematic uncertainty should be
considered.
A liquid H(2) target of 87.3 mg/cm**2 thickness was
used.
In order to subtract the contribution due to nuclear
reactions in the windows of the target, an additional
dummy target was used, simulating the material and
thickness of the windows (titanium 36 mg/cm**2).
